    <body>
      <head>Lugano</head>
      <div>

        <p>Town in the Ticino district of southern Switzerland, situated on Lake Lugano and
          surrounded by mountains. Lugano lies close to the Italian border, and is c.60 km (c.40
          miles) north of Milan. Since 1882 it was a stop on the Gotthard Railway.</p>

        <p>In October 1924, <ref cRef="entity-000643">Reinhard Oppel</ref>’s wife <ref
            cRef="entity-006150">Gertrud</ref> was sent by train from <ref cRef="entity-002757"
            >Kiel</ref> to Lugano to recover from a serious illness, and died there in August
          1925.</p>

        <p>From 1929, <ref cRef="entity-000922">Otto Vrieslander</ref> and his wife <ref
            cRef="entity-000921">Hélène</ref> lived in Tegna, north east of Lugano, where <ref
            cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref> visited them in September 1936, as recorded
          in her Travel Diary.</p>


      </div>
